<p> Revs		     318,129		  313,128</p>
<p> Avg shrs		  38,476		   30,598</p>
<p>(All data above 000s except per share numbers)</p>
<p>NOTE: The company said on June 30, 1997 it acquired Texas Instruments Software and terminated its distributor agreement with Sterling Commerce Inc.  Results for the current periods include a reorganization charge of $107,037,000 and $137,849,000 in research and development costs.</p>
<p>The company said its tax benefit related to the acquisition charge was $39,737,000.</p>
<p>Current periods ended June 30, 1997.</p>
<p>Full name is Sterling Software Inc.</p>
